The Thayan Language

thayin thayan /θeˈɪjɪn/

The lanugage script is an adjusted version of the Barazhad script

Spelling & Phonology

Consonant inventory:

b d f h j k l m n p q r s sˤ t tˤ w x z ð ħ ɣ ʃ ʔ ʤ θ

↓Manner/Place→ Bilabial Labiodental Dental Alveolar Palato-alveolar Palatal Velar Uvular Pharyngeal Glottal
Nasal m n
Stop p b t tˤ d k q ʔ
Affricate ʤ
Fricative f θ ð s sˤ z ʃ x ɣ ħ h
Approximant j
Trill r
Lateral approximant l

Co-articulated phonemes

↓Manner/Place→ Labial-velar
Approximant w

Vowel inventory: a aː e eɪ̯ i iː o u uː ɪ ʊ ʌ

Diphthongs : eɪ̯

Front Back
High i iː u uː
Near-high ɪ ʊ
High-mid e o
Low-mid ʌ
Low a aː
Spelling rules:

Pronunciation ʔ a eɪ aː ɪn b d ð tˤ e i iː f ɣ h ɪ ʤ k x l m n o uː u p q r s ʃ sˤ t θ ʊ ʌ w ħ j z
Spelling ' a a ā in b d dh dt e ē ē f gh h i j k kh l m n o ū u p q r s sh sz t th u u w xh y z
Transliteration ' a a aa an b d dh dt e ee ee f gh h i j k kh l m n o oo ou p q r s sh sz t th u u w xh y z

Grammar

Sentence word order: Verb-Indirect object-Direct object-Subject. “She gave the dog a bone” turns into Gave the dog a bone she .
Adjective order: Adjectives are positioned before the noun.
Adposition: postpositions

Gender

Numbers

Thayan has a base-6 number system:

1 - do do
2 - ha ha
3 - ho ho
4 - da da
5 - sha sha
6 - mēm meem
36 - khurad khurad
216 - jalēr jaleer

Derivational morphology

Adjective → adverb = Suffix -o
Adjective → noun (the quality of being [adj]) = Suffix -ab
Adjective → verb (to make something [adj]) = Suffix -iː
Noun → adjective (having the quality of [noun]) = If starts with vowel: Prefix is-
Else: Prefix isi-
Noun → adjective relating to noun (e.g. economy → economic) = If starts with vowel: Prefix n-
Else: Prefix ne-
Noun to verb = If ends with vowel: Suffix -jj
Else: Suffix -awjj
Verb → adjective (result of doing [verb]) = Suffix -id
Tending to = If ends with vowel: Suffix -b
Else: Suffix -ub
Verb → noun (the act of [verb]) = If ends with vowel: Suffix -m
Else: Suffix -im
Verb → noun that verb produces (e.g. know → knowledge) = If ends with vowel: Suffix -r
Else: Suffix -ur
One who [verb]s (e.g. paint → painter) = Suffix -asij
Place of (e.g. wine → winery) = If ends with vowel: Suffix -ba
Else: Suffix -uːba
Diminutive = If ends with vowel: Suffix -ʃu
Else: Suffix -awʃu
Augmentative = If ends with vowel: Suffix -r
Else: Suffix -ur
Opposite = If ends with vowel: Suffix -m
Else: Suffix -iːm
Arcane = If starts with vowel: Prefix tˤ-
Else: Prefix tˤuː-
Divine = Suffix -e
Fiendish = If ends with vowel: Suffix -l
Else: Suffix -uːl
Magical = Suffix -uː
Bestial = If starts with vowel: Prefix n-
Else: Prefix no-
Superior = If ends with vowel: Suffix -ʤ
Else: Suffix -iːʤ
Inferior = Prefix e-
Many = Prefix eɪ̯-
Combination = If ends with vowel: Suffix -s
Else: Suffix -os
